The paper deals with the problem of coordinating agents to complete tasks with temporal and resource constraints, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed involves learning heuristics from human domain experts, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of human-machine collaboration, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
